header.gameNote: SMU HOLIDAY CLASSIC AT DALLAS TX

article.headline: Texas St. 113, Paul Quinn 87
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Jonathan Sloan scored 23 points to lead Texas State to a 113-87 win over Paul Quinn on Sunday. Sloan was 7 of 13 from the field and hit 9 of 10 free throws. Brandon Bush added 19 points and 12 rebounds for the Bobcats (7-5). Ty Gough scored 13 points and Brent Benson had 11. Jazz Henderson scored 27 points, including 14 of 15 free throws, to lead Paul Quinn (6-8). Jackie Ransom scored 16 points, and Larry Ivey had 14 for the Tigers, who play in the NAIA. The Bobcats dominated the boards, hauling down 58 rebounds to Paul Quinn's 42. The Tigers, who were plagued by 37 percent shooting, were behind 59-42 at the half. The Bobcats shot 48 percent.
